In some of the chapters you might need something known as a storage account.

We will go through storage accounts in an upcoming section, but to quickly create a storage account, one can go through the following steps

1) Go ahead to Azure and go the section on storage accounts


2) Next go ahead to create a new storage account


3) Specify the below settings for the storage account


Specify an existing resource group

Ensure to give a unique name for the storage account

Specify the location which would the same as the location for the Virtual machine for which you are going to enable the backup for

Ensure to specify the Performance as Standard

Ensure the account kind is StorageV2

Ensure the replication is Locally-redundant storage

Define the access tier as Hot

4) Keep the Networking details as default


5) Keep the Advanced settings as default


Then you can go ahead and create the storage account.


